event.title: was assigned a parcel of the land in 1831

data.event: Thomas William Mews was assigned a parcel of the land in 1831.
Mews could not fulfil the required duties, and the grant passed to TRC Walters in 1840.
In 1842 the locality was named 'Jackadup', the Aboriginal name for the area.
Development in Woodlands started in the 1960s.
The Floreat Lakes Estate to the south east was subdivided in 1991.
Part of the area that is now Woodlands was originally assigned to Thomas William Mews in 1831.

event.title: passed to T. R. C. Walters in 1840

data.event: However, as Mews could not fulfil the location duties, the grant passed to T. R. C. Walters in 1840.
